11#ifndef CALL_RTX_RECEIVE_STREAM_H_
12#define CALL_RTX_RECEIVE_STREAM_H_
13
14#include <cstdint>
15#include <map>
16
17#include "call/rtp_packet_sink_interface.h"
18
19namespace webrtc {
20
21class ReceiveStatistics;
22
23// This class is responsible for RTX decapsulation. The resulting media packets
24// are passed on to a sink representing the associated media stream.
25class RtxReceiveStream : public RtpPacketSinkInterface {
26 public:
27 RtxReceiveStream(RtpPacketSinkInterface* media_sink,
28 std::map<int, int> associated_payload_types,
29 uint32_t media_ssrc,
30 // TODO(nisse): Delete this argument, and
31 // corresponding member variable, by moving the
32 // responsibility for rtcp feedback to
33 // RtpStreamReceiverController.
34 ReceiveStatistics* rtp_receive_statistics = nullptr);
35 ~RtxReceiveStream() override;
36 // RtpPacketSinkInterface.
37 void OnRtpPacket(const RtpPacketReceived& packet) override;
38
39 private:
40 RtpPacketSinkInterface* const media_sink_;
41 // Map from rtx payload type -> media payload type.
42 const std::map<int, int> associated_payload_types_;
43 // TODO(nisse): Ultimately, the media receive stream shouldn't care about the
44 // ssrc, and we should delete this.
45 const uint32_t media_ssrc_;
46 ReceiveStatistics* const rtp_receive_statistics_;
47};
48
49} // namespace webrtc
50
51#endif // CALL_RTX_RECEIVE_STREAM_H_
